    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between pairing wine with white meat versus dark meat chicken?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">White meat chicken (breast) has delicate flavors that pair beautifully with lighter wines like Chardonnay, Pinot Grigio, or Pinot Noir, while dark meat (thighs, legs) has richer, more intense flavors that can handle fuller-bodied wines like Côtes du Rhône, Zinfandel, or even light Cabernet Sauvignon. The higher fat content in dark meat also complements wines with more tannins and structure. Consider the cooking method too—grilled dark meat can even pair well with medium-bodied reds.</p>
